[1] Brazil
Date: 29 Feb 2008
Source: Diario de Manha Online [trans. & edited]
<http://www.dm.com.br/ultimas.php?id=57390>


Another death by yellow fever confirmed in Goias state
------------------------------------------------------
The Department of Health confirmed one more fatal
case of yellow fever in the State. The victim was
a housewife aged 65, living on a farm in
Cristianopolis, 90 km [56 miles] from Goiania
[the state capital]. According to the management
of the Department of Epidemiological
Surveillance, when the health team sought her in
the rural area to offer the vaccine, she refused
to be immunized on religious grounds. The woman
began to feel the first symptoms of the disease
on 13 Jan 2008. On 19 Jan 2008 she died in a
hospital in Goiania.

[Initial] lab tests were performed at the Evandro
Chagas Institute of Para, and they were all
negative. On this Thursday [28 Feb 2008], the
last laboratory test, immunohistochemistry, came
out positive. With this new case, the number of
deaths from yellow fever in Goias in 2008 rises
to 10, out of 17 confirmed cases.

In 2007, 7 cases of yellow fever were confirmed, of which 6 died.

--
Communicated by:
LISAS


[At the close of 28 Feb 2008, the official count
was 60 cases including 24 deaths notified, 35
cases including 19 deaths confirmed, 23 cases
including 3 deaths discounted, and 2 fatal cases
still under investigation -- see:
<http://portal.saude.gov.br/portal/arquivos/pdf/boletimfa_280208.pdf>.

It is not clear whether the case above is one of
the 2 fatal cases under investigation. - Mod.JW]

