[3] Paraguay (WHO)
Date: 28 Feb 2008
Source: WHO Epidemic and Pandemic Alert and
Response (EPR) Outbreak News [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2008_02_28a/en/index.html>


Yellow fever in Paraguay - update
Mobilization against Yellow Fever in Paraguay Continues
-------------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Public Health and Social Welfare
(MSPBS) of Paraguay has reported the confirmation
of 16 cases of yellow fever (YF), including 3
deaths; 7 of these cases, young people who
visited rural areas, are from the Department of
San Pedro, and are related to the jungle cycle of
the virus. The other 9 confirmed cases, which
include the 3 deaths, are from San Lorenzo
Municipality, outside of Asunci√≥n. Another 15
suspected cases are being investigated.

Meanwhile, the Ministry of Health is taking
measures to contain the disease in affected
areas, and more than 1 million people who live in
or travel to these affected areas have been
vaccinated. The Ministry of Health obtained 2
million doses of yellow fever vaccine from the
International Coordinating Group on Provision of
Vaccines of the World Health Organization. Brazil
sent 850 000 doses and Peru sent 144 000 doses of
vaccines, adding to the 300 000 Paraguay had in
reserve.

For more information see:
PAHO Press release
Pan American Health Organization
Regional Office for the Americas of the World Health Organization
<http://www.paho.org>

