[4] Paraguay (Asuncion)
Date: 29 Feb 2008
Source: ANSA America [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.JW, edited]
<http://www.ansa.it/ansalatina/notizie/notiziari/paraguay/20080229171534605490.html>


The Paraguayan Ministry of Public Health today
reported 6 new cases of suspected yellow fever in
Asuncion and its environs.

Health authorities had under surveillance about
15 cases, of which 4 have been discounted today,
physician Antonio Arbo, coordinator of the
national campaign against the disease, told the
press.

Local newspapers listed 8 dead, while the
Ministry of Public Health confirmed only 5.

Last week [25-29 Feb 2008] more than a million
people were immunized, and a few days ago the
government received 2 million more doses of the
vaccine from the World Health Organization, which
is calming the hysteria caused by the appearance
of the 1st fatal cases and the [initial] lack of
vaccine.

--
